# Testing Guidelines

## Test Framework

This project uses:

- **Mocha** - Test runner
- **Chai** - Assertion library

## Running Tests

```bash
npm install  # Install dependencies
npm test     # Run all tests
```

## Test File Structure

Test files are located in `test/src/` and named with `.test.js` suffix:

- [author.test.js](mdc:test/src/author.test.js) - Tests for Author class
- [mailservice.duck.test.js](mdc:test/src/mailservice.duck.test.js) - Tests for DuckDuckGo mail service
- [mailservice.proton.test.js](mdc:test/src/mailservice.proton.test.js) - Tests for ProtonMail service
- [recipientinitial.test.js](mdc:test/src/recipientinitial.test.js) - Tests for RecipientInitial class

## Test Structure

### Basic Test Template

```javascript
import { expect } from "chai";
import ClassName from "../../src/src/ClassName.js";

describe("ClassName", () => {
  describe("methodName", () => {
    it("should do something specific", () => {
      // Arrange
      const instance = new ClassName();
      const input = "test";

      // Act
      const result = instance.methodName(input);

      // Assert
      expect(result).to.equal("expected");
    });
  });
});
```

### Async Tests

```javascript
describe("AsyncClass", () => {
  it("should fetch data asynchronously", async () => {
    const instance = new AsyncClass();
    const result = await instance.fetchData();
    expect(result).to.not.be.null;
  });
});
```

## Assertion Styles

### Equality

```javascript
expect(value).to.equal(expected); // Strict equality (===)
expect(value).to.deep.equal(expected); // Deep equality for objects/arrays
expect(value).to.eql(expected); // Alias for deep.equal
```

### Truthiness

```javascript
expect(value).to.be.true;
expect(value).to.be.false;
expect(value).to.be.null;
expect(value).to.be.undefined;
expect(value).to.exist;
expect(value).to.not.exist;
```

### Type Checking

```javascript
expect(value).to.be.a("string");
expect(value).to.be.an("array");
expect(value).to.be.an.instanceof(ClassName);
```

### Strings

```javascript
expect(str).to.include("substring");
expect(str).to.match(/regex/);
expect(str).to.have.lengthOf(10);
```

### Arrays and Objects

```javascript
expect(array).to.have.lengthOf(3);
expect(array).to.include(item);
expect(array).to.have.members([1, 2, 3]);
expect(obj).to.have.property("key");
expect(obj).to.have.property("key", "value");
expect(obj).to.have.keys(["key1", "key2"]);
```

