```

### Test Edge Cases

Always test:

- Normal inputs
- Empty values
- Null/undefined
- Special characters
- Edge cases specific to domain

```javascript
describe("RecipientInitial", () => {
  describe("getInitials", () => {
    it("should get initials from normal name", () => {
      expect(getInitials("John Doe")).to.equal("JD");
    });

    it("should handle single name", () => {
      expect(getInitials("John")).to.equal("J");
    });

    it("should handle empty string", () => {
      expect(getInitials("")).to.equal("");
    });

    it("should handle special characters", () => {
      expect(getInitials("Jean-Paul François")).to.equal("JF");
    });
  });
});
```

## Testing Providers

### Provider Test Pattern

```javascript
describe("GravatarProvider", () => {
  let provider;

  beforeEach(() => {
    provider = new GravatarProvider();
  });

  it("should have correct scope", () => {
    expect(provider.scope).to.equal(Scope.EMAIL);
  });

  it("should generate valid URL for email", async () => {
    const author = await Author.fromAuthor("user@example.com");
    const url = await provider.getUrl(author);
    expect(url).to.be.a("string");
    expect(url).to.include("gravatar.com");
  });

  it("should handle missing avatar gracefully", async () => {
    const author = await Author.fromAuthor("nonexistent@example.com");
    const url = await provider.getUrl(author);
    // Should return URL even if avatar doesn't exist (provider handles 404)
    expect(url).to.not.be.null;
  });
});
```

## Testing Services

### Mock Dependencies

```javascript
describe("AvatarService", () => {
  let avatarService;
  let mockProfileFetcher;

  beforeEach(() => {
    avatarService = new AvatarService();
    mockProfileFetcher = {
      getAvatar: async () => "http://example.com/avatar.jpg",
    };
  });

  it("should cache avatar URLs", async () => {
    const author = await Author.fromAuthor("user@example.com");
    const url1 = await avatarService.getAvatar(author);
    const url2 = await avatarService.getAvatar(author);
    expect(url1).to.equal(url2); // Should return cached value
  });
});
```

## Testing Email Parsing

Test various email formats:

```javascript
describe("Author.fromAuthor", () => {
  it("should parse plain email", async () => {
    const author = await Author.fromAuthor("user@example.com");
    expect(author.getAuthor()).to.equal("user@example.com");
  });

  it("should parse email with display name", async () => {
    const author = await Author.fromAuthor("John Doe <john@example.com>");
    expect(author.getAuthor()).to.equal("john@example.com");
  });

  it("should handle ProtonMail addresses", async () => {
    const author = await Author.fromAuthor("user@pm.me");
    expect(author.getDomain()).to.equal("protonmail.com");
  });

  it("should handle DuckDuckGo addresses", async () => {
    const author = await Author.fromAuthor("user@duck.com");
    expect(author.getDomain()).to.equal("duckduckgo.com");
  });
});
```

## Performance Tests

Test for performance issues:

```javascript
describe("CacheStorage", () => {
  it("should retrieve from cache quickly", async () => {
    const cache = new CacheStorage();
    const start = Date.now();

    await cache.set("key", "value");
    const value = await cache.get("key");

    const duration = Date.now() - start;
    expect(duration).to.be.below(100); // Should complete in < 100ms
  });
});
```

## Test Coverage

Aim for high coverage of:

- ✅ Core business logic (Author, RecipientInitial)
- ✅ Provider URL generation
- ✅ Email parsing edge cases
- ✅ Cache operations
- ✅ Error handling

Lower priority:

- UI rendering code (test manually in Thunderbird)
- Network requests (use mocks)
- Browser API calls (stub if needed)

## Before Committing

Always run tests before committing:

```bash
npm test
```

All tests should pass:

```
  56 passing
```

## Adding New Tests

When adding new features:

1. Write tests first (TDD approach) or alongside implementation
2. Test happy path and edge cases
3. Ensure tests are independent (no shared state)
4. Use descriptive test names
5. Add to existing test files or create new ones following naming convention

## Debugging Tests

### Run Single Test File

```bash
npx mocha test/src/author.test.js
```

### Run Tests with Grep

```bash
npx mocha --grep "getInitials"
```

### Add Debug Output

```javascript
it("should do something", () => {
  console.log("Debug:", variable); // Add temporary debug logs
  expect(result).to.equal(expected);
});
```

## CI/CD Considerations

Tests should be:

- Fast (complete in < 10 seconds total)
- Deterministic (no random failures)
- Independent (no reliance on external services)
- Self-contained (no manual setup required)
